rComments: To be honest I found this particular class extremely boring. The material is incredibly dry. Orchard is very monotone, kind of lacks a personality. However, he is a nice guy and is very willing to help you with any questions, good with giving extensions on assignments. Lectures are easy to follow along.

not necessarily the most engaging, but was very approachable and seemed to genuinely care about the success of his students. lectures were generally taught right from slides and it was easy to do well just by memorizing the slides. some exam questions, however, did seem to come right from left-field, but overall were reasonable... know his maps!
